PrecisRe-appointment of Leo Hardy, of Kelowna, British Columbia, as a member of the Western Aboriginal Economic Development Board and designation of the said Leo Hardy as Chairperson thereof, for a term of three years, effective February 10, 1992; re-appointment of certain persons as members of the Western Aboriginal Economic Development Board for a term of three years, effective February 10, 1992; and appointment of certain persons as members of the Western Aboriginal Economic Development Board for a term of three years. (Phillip Asp, Dease Lake, British Columbia; Ron Rivard, Saskatoon, Saskatchewan; Ronald D. Williams, Yellowknife, Northwest Territories; Charles S. Coffey, Winnipeg, Manitoba; and Mark Wallace Wedge, Carcross, Yukon Territory)
